This paper is about reinforcement learning algorithms, specifically off-policy policy gradient algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which includes papers on reinforcement learning. The paper also involves deep RL benchmarks, which suggests it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of robot simulation tasks suggests it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves the use of mathematical proofs, which suggests it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves the use of empirical experiments, which suggests it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
